article.headline: Bucknell 70, Loyola, Md. 59
article.story: BALTIMORE -- G.W. Boon and Joe Willman scored 16 points apiece as Bucknell defeated Loyola (Md.) 70-59 on Tuesday night. The Bison (7-7), coming off an 84-80 loss to Boston College, have won five of their last six games. The Greyhounds (4-8) have lost three in a row and six of their last seven. Loyola led 12-2 as Bucknell missed its first five shots, but the Bison used a 14-3 run, including seven points from Boon, to pull ahead. Bucknell, which shot 52.4 percent in the first half (11 of 21), closed the first half on a 15-2 run to lead 36-27. The Bison extended the lead to 47-31 with 14:56 to go. Loyola's 8-0 run cut the gap to eight points, but the Greyhounds could get no closer. The Bison made 7 of 8 free throws in the final 2:37. Bryson Johnson had 13 points for Bucknell and Mike Muscala added 10 rebounds. Shane Walker had 14 points and nine rebounds for Loyola.
